title: For Sale:  Husqvarna 30-06 w/ Scope
postcontent:
This is a classic Husqvarna commercial mauser chambered in the ever popular 30-06 Springfield.  What makes this rifle a treat is that it is all original…it maintains the front sight hood (which is often removed and lost), the rear sight with elevation ladder (also often removed and lost), and the crown butt plate (which is often replaced with a soft recoil pad for the meek).  This rifle was manufactured in 1952, during the days when Husqvarna was using FN commercial actions to build their rifles.  As quoted by Frank de Haas in his book Bolt Action Rifles, “FN actions are made to the usual exacting FN quality, a quality so outstanding that no one should question it”.  And for the quality of the rifle as a whole, Ludwig Olsen in his book Mauser Bolt Rifles had this to say…”Some of the finest Mauser sporting rifles and carbines were made by Husqvarna Vapenfabriks, A. B., Huskvarna, Sweden”.  To further attest to the quality of Husky rifles…back in the day, Husqvarna used to “battle it out” with Sako of Finland, and anybody familiar with Sako rifles knows the kind of quality and price they demand.  Unfortunately, due to the radical change of the social and political atmosphere of Sweden towards firearms back in the 70s, Husqvarna (the world’s second oldest firearms manufacturer) stopped producing firearms to venture into other products. 

As for the rifle itself…the stock is in great condition with no cracks or splits and only the usual handling marks you would expect from normal use.  The checkering on the forearm and grip is still sharp and the butt plate is free of cracks or broken off pieces.  The barrel and receiver are free of rust or pitting and the bluing is spectacular.  The action is smooth and lock up is tight.  The bore is clean with good rifling.  It is outfitted with a vintage Weaver KV scope which is damage free with good optics.  All in all, this rifle is a treasure that can be cherished and proudly passed on from one generation to the next (can’t say that about the cheap synthetic crap they make nowadays).  

Not interested in trades at this time.  Located in Enterprise.

title: For Sale/Trade:  *Must sell* Norinco SKS in Tapco stock/sight mount/sight rings and ammo
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade I have a Norinco SKS that has been fitted into a tapco stock. The rifle has had parts replaces by me, so the gas piston/piston block, firing pin, recoil spring, and extractor are all new. This is a really great firing gun, but as with any firearm that is it's age there are a few scratches mainly just on the receiver where the latch is moved to take the piston apart for cleaning. The rifle has the original cleaning rod from when it rolled off production lines in China, and it has all matching serial numbers. The rifling is still nice and deep, and although the rifle doesn't need it, I have always cleaned it and oiled it up nice after each range trip. The bolt is in great shape and so is the inside of the receiver.

In addition to the rifle, I also have a 30 round tapco SKS magazine that has been fitted to the stock, and can be installed by simply pressing a button to remove the trigger group, pull the standard 10 round factory mag out, and then replace the trigger group. From there you are able to use the removable magazines available and negate having to use stripper clips or load by hand. I also have a scope mount and rings that fit into the already tapped area on the back of the receiver, and the piston block has a standard rail built into it for the use of a red dot or other optic. I can also toss in 110 rounds of FMJ ammo and 100 rounds of hollow point ammo as well.

I have reduced the asking price down to $375 or best offer ($550 put into the weapon) for the work I put into the rifle, new stock (sadly the wooden one was trashed when I got the rifle), new firing pin, new extractor, scope mount, and tapping the receiver for said scope. I have plenty of pictures (since I can only upload three) and can send them upon request. You can reach me at my email listed on here, or by text or phone at 77zero-54nine-596three (apologies, trying to avoid bots). Don't think it's a fair price, go ahead and offer me something. As long as it's reasonable then I'll accept.
